title: IndyCar Series - 2014 Honda Indy Toronto (Race 2) [720p / PT-BR]
description:
That's the second race that happened in Toronto, Canada, holding the Round 14 of 2014 Indycar Series. As I mentioned, that race was a way funnier than the first one on Sunday Morning due to the light-medium rain that fell on the track in the middle of the race which made teams crew's changing their strategies. As soon as the track dried out over the final part of the race, Mike Conway was one of the first drivers to change his tyres back to slicks. Therefore, he could lead his way to the victory. Also a great performance of Tony Kanaan and a huge battle between Will Power and Helio Castroneves who ended up having part of front wing broken, costing him a lot of points in Drivers Championship. Tons of incidents also occured in this race such as on Lap 18, involving several cars including Montoya. Brazilian Full Coverage, commentated by Nivaldo Prieto and Sergio Ximenez.
